üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. ITAA 2008 is an amendment to the:
A. IPC
B. IT Act 2000
C. Companies Act
D. RBI Act

2. The primary objective of ITAA 2008 is to:
A. Regulate banking
B. Address cyber crimes and electronic transactions
C. Enforce data localization
D. Replace GDPR

3. Which section of IT Act deals with data protection and compensation?
A. Section 43A
B. Section 66
C. Section 72
D. Section 79

4. DPDP Act 2023 primarily governs:
A. Financial fraud
B. Digital personal data of individuals
C. Network security
D. Software licensing

5. DPDP Act 2023 applies to:
A. Offline paper records only
B. Digital personal data processing
C. Government data only
D. Non-personal data

6. In DPDP Act, the individual to whom data relates is called:
A. Data controller
B. Data processor
C. Data principal
D. Data fiduciary

7. A global bank internal audit mainly focuses on:
A. Coding practices
B. Risk, compliance, and control effectiveness
C. Hardware procurement
D. Marketing

8. Anti-corruption compliance focuses on preventing:
A. Malware attacks
B. Bribery and unethical practices
C. Data breaches
D. Phishing

9. Case studies in CCEE exams are used to test:
A. Memorization
B. Application of concepts
C. Tool usage
D. Coding skills

10. ITAA 2008 applies within:
A. Only government organizations
B. India
C. European Union
D. Globally

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)
11. Section 43A of IT Act mandates:
A. Encryption
B. Reasonable security practices
C. Breach notification
D. Data localization

