A. Only internal policies
B. RBI, international laws, and standards
C. Developer guidelines
D. Hardware lifecycle

16. Anti-corruption audit checks typically include:
A. Incident response
B. Gifts, bribery, and third-party risks
C. Network logs
D. Malware scans

17. DPDP Act emphasizes which core principle?
A. Data maximization
B. Purpose limitation and consent
C. Unlimited storage
D. Anonymous processing

18. Internal audit solutions are generally:
A. Reactive
B. Risk-based and continuous
C. Tool-driven only
D. External only

19. Compliance audit case studies usually require:
A. One correct answer
B. Best-fit solution based on scenario
C. Tool configuration
D. Code writing

20. DPDP Act is closer in nature to:
A. PCI DSS
B. GDPR
C. ITIL
D. COBIT

